node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Suki Cat on December 08, 2020 tagging @barcsrescue_calgary. Image may contain: dog.

node.text:
Everyone, meet Killua- Suki’s new big sister! 😻 This sweet girl is so full of love, and has been settling in well since we picked her up on Saturday. At the moment she is a little unsure about how to act around Suki, so we are keeping a close eye on them both until we get to know Killua better. Suki has already accepted her as a friend and will go up to her for nose boops... and will try to steal her treats before we can stop her! 😽
Killua is a 4 year old stray from the streets of California, but you would never guess it when meeting her. We are so excited for all of the amazing adventures to come! 🥰🐕
.
I’d like to give a huge thank you to @barcsrescue_calgary and her amazing foster family for saving and taking care of Killua. She has already melted our hearts, and is in for a lifetime of love and exciting adventures! 💓
